Cross-compiler toolchain installed here.


steps:


versions tried: 
X	gcc4.6.2 with binutils 2.22
X	gcc4.0.1 with binutils 2.16
X	gcc4.0.1 with binutils 2.22
gcc4.4.3 with binutils 2.20.1





Installing binutils
------------------------------------------------
1. install binutils version 2.16
	download binutils-2.16.1.tar.bz2 from http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/binutils/
	store it in /usr/local/cross/tar

2. extract in usr/local/cross/src/ by the following:
	bunzip2 binutils-2.16.1.tar.bz2
	then tar -xvf binutils-2.16.1.tar

3. mkdir /usr/local/cross/src/binutils-2.16.1_build

4. cd  /usr/local/cross/src/binutils-2.16.1_build

5. ../binutils-2.16.1/configure --target=sparc-elf --prefix=/usr/local/cross

6. this will create a Makefile. Now make followed by su root, make install
---------------------------------------------------




Installing gcc version 4.0.1
--------------------------------------------------------
1. download gcc-4.0.1.tar.bz2 from http://mirrors.rcn.net/pub/sourceware/gcc/releases/gcc-4.0.1/
	store it in /usr/local/cross/tar

2. extract in usr/local/cross/src/ by the following:
	bunzip2 gcc-4.0.1.tar.bz2
	then tar -xvf gcc-4.0.1.tar

3. mkdir /usr/local/cross/src/gcc-4.0.1_build

4. cd /usr/local/cross/src/gcc-4.0.1_build

5  ../gcc-4.0.1/configure --target=sparc-elf --with-newlib --without-headers --with-gnu-as --with-gnu-ld --enable-languages=c,c++ --disable-nls --prefix=/usr/local/cross


6. this will create a Makefile. Now make followed by su root, make install

if there's a spar-ar not found error:
$> PATH=/usr/local/cross/bin:${PATH} make

$> PATH=/usr/local/cross/bin:${PATH} make install

---------------------------------------------------


Finally what worked:

binutils 2.20.1
gmp 5.0.2
mpfr 3.1.0
mpc 0.9
gcc4.4.3 

1. binutils installed fine.
2. unzip gcc 
3. download gmp, mpc and mpfr. unzip each and rename folder to /gmp /mpfr /mpc.
4. move all these folders inside the gcc source folder.
5. make a gcc_build folder and run ../gcc_source-folder/configure ...flags
6. inside the build folder run make and make install.
7. you might need to do
 PATH=/usr/local/cross/bin:${PATH} make




gcc configuration flags:

~$ sparc-elf-gcc -v

Using built-in specs.
Target: sparc-elf
Configured with: ../gcc-4.4.3/configure --target=sparc-elf --with-newlib
--with-gnu-as --with-gnu-ld --enable-languages=c --disable-nls
--prefix=/usr/local/cross --disable-multilib
--with-mpfr-lib=/usr/local/cross/lib
--with-mpfr-include=/usr/local/cross/include --without-headers --disable-libssp
Thread model: single
gcc version 4.4.3 (GCC)
nehak@nehak:~$





